    <Investigation>
        <name>Venera 3</name>
        <type>Mission</type>
        <start_date>1965-11-16</start_date>
        <stop_date>1966-03-01</stop_date>
        <description>

Venera 3 mission intended to explore Venus and land on the surface.
The Soviet Venera 3 mission comprised a carrier bus and an attached
descent craft (lander probe). The lander probe impacted Venus on
1 March 1966, making Venera 3 the first spacecraft to reach the
surface of another planet. However, the communications systems had
failed on 16 February, before planetary data could be returned.

        </description>
